comments: Powell (DAL) legally contests Huerter's (SAC) driving shot attempt.  Marginal contact occurs as a result of Huerter extending his off-arm.
Davis (SAC) reaches in and gets his fingertips on the ball.  Doncic (DAL) briefly loses his balance while protecting the ball and any contact between the two players is marginal.
Fox (SAC) cleanly deflects the ball away from Bullock (DAL) and steals the pass.
Replay review of the foul called on Davis (SAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Davis (SAC) grabs Powell's (DAL) arm, affecting his FOM.
Green (DAL) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Sabonis (SAC) grabs Powell (DAL), affecting his SQBR after he grabs the rebound.
Sabonis (SAC) firms up in a screening position in Bullock's (DAL) path and does not deliver contact.

Powell (DAL) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact that occurs with Fox (SAC) during his driving shot attempt.  Powell is turned as a result of the two players coming together and he does not turn into Fox.
Davis (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Doncic (DAL) during the drive.
Huerter (SAC) contests Bullock's (DAL) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Sabonis (SAC) establishes himself in Green's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Irving (DAL) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Green (DAL) initiates contact to Fox's (SAC) body that affects his SQBR during his shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) briefly extends an arm towards Doncic (DAL), who raises his own arm into it.  The contact between the two players is marginal.
Sabonis (SAC) extends an arm into Doncic's (DAL) front, affecting his SQBR.
Fox (SAC) extends an arm towards Irving's (DAL) front, but the contact during the drive is marginal.
Barnes (SAC) contests the shot attempt at the basket by Powell (DAL) and marginal body contact occurs.
Doncic (DAL) and Lyles (SAC) both reach for the rebound and incidental arm contact occurs.
Upon controlling the rebound, Fox (SAC) turns around and marginal contact occurs with Powell (DAL), who is not in an illegal position.
Bullock (DAL) gets his hand on the ball as Fox (SAC) attempts to regain control and a held ball is correctly whistled.
Lyles (SAC) maintains his pivot foot.
Huerter (SAC) places an arm against Irving (DAL) during the rebound but does not dislodge him from his position.
Irving (DAL) moves towards Huerter (SAC) and marginal body contact occurs during his shot attempt at the rim.
Irving (DAL) moves forward into Fox (SAC) and initiates body contact that affects his SQBR.
Fox (SAC) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.  Any marginal contact is created by Doncic extending his leg.
Ntilikina (DAL) commits a take foul on Fox (SAC).
Davis (SAC) briefly places a hand on Doncic's (DAL) back, but the contact is marginal.
Pinson (DAL) commits a take foul on Fox (SAC).
